TYPE-A PERSONALITY.Definition: a person with behavior and personality associated with high achievement, competitiveness, and impatience

PATHETIC.Definition: sad; marked by sorrow or melancholy

LEISURELY.Definition: used to describe an action that is done in a relaxed way, without hurrying

SUSTAINABLE.Definition: to be able to continue over a period of time

GENIUS.Definition: very great and rare natural ability or skill, especially in a particular are

INTUITIVELY.Definition: (knowledge from) an ability to understand or know something immediately based on your feelings rather than facts

BORING.Definition: causing weariness and restlessness through lack of interest

DOUBLE DOWN.Definition: strengthen one's commitment to a particular strategy or course of action, typically one that is potentially risky

OBVIOUS.Definition: easily perceived or understood; clear, self-evident, or apparent

LEGIT.Definition: short for legitimate, genuine, actual or literal

REVENUE STREAM.Definition: a particular means by which a company or individual generates revenue on an ongoing basis

INVEST.Definition: to put money, effort, time, etc.

EXECUTE.Definition: carry out or put into effect (a plan, order, or course of action)

SHORTSIGHTED.Definition: not thinking enough about how an action will affect the future

NEGLECT.Definition: not give enough care or attention to something

CONQUER THE WORLD.Definition: achieve greatness, to deal with or successfully overcome problems

ASPIRATIONS.Definition: something that you hope to achieve

VISIONS.Definition: an idea or mental image of something

UNCONVENTIONAL.Definition: different from what is usual or from the way most people do things

WEIRD.Definition: very strange and unusual, unexpected, or not natural

BURNT OUT.Definition: very tired from working too hard

BUMP YOUR HEAD ON A LOT OF WALLS.Definition: face a lot of problems or difficulties

LAUNCHED.Definition: begin something such as a plan or introduce something new

INTENTION.Definition: aim; something that you want and plan to do

IMAGINARY.Definition: created by and exists only in the mind

REALISTIC.Definition: practical idea of what can be achieved or expected

CONFUSION.Definition: a situation in which people do not understand what is happening, what they should do or who someone or something is

DOUBTS.Definition: (a feeling of) not being certain about something

OBLIGATED.Definition: having the feeling that it is one's duty to do something

CHORE.Definition: a task that you must do but that you find unpleasant or boring

BULLSHIT.Definition: a slang term for something stupid or untrue

OVERWHELMING.Definition: something that affects you very strongly, and you do not know how to deal with it

COMFORT ZONE.Definition: a situation in which you feel comfortable and you do not have to do anything new or difficult

HUSTLE AND BUSTLE.Definition: large amount of activity and work

HESITATE.Definition: hold back in doubt or indecision
